Malaya - Singapore v. 1.2

Just after Pearl Harbour, the Japanese forces striked on the Malayan peninsula. After weeks of fighting into the jungle, the British forces loss the whole peninsula, and then the fortress city of Singapore. Winston Churchill said that this was the worst chapter in the military history of the United Kingdom.

This scenario offers you the opportunity to manage the Japanase assault or to defend the Malayan Peninsula.

Autor: Santiago Fuertes

Konversion in OG: M. Kessler
